2 (11) Notwithstanding any other statute to the contrary, if available funds are insufficient
3 for all requested scholarships for eligible applicants during any fiscal year, the
4 authority shall give priority consideration to eligible applicants who previously
5 received teacher scholarships and, until June 30, 2018, to loan forgiveness for
6 teachers who have outstanding loan balance eligibility for Best in Class loans issued
7 prior to June 30, 2008. If funds are insufficient to make all requested renewal
8 scholarships to eligible applicants, the authority shall reduce all scholarship awards
9 to the extent necessary to provide scholarships to all qualified renewal applicants.
10 If, after awarding all eligible renewal applicants, funds are not depleted, initial
11 applications shall be ranked according to regulatory selection criteria, which may
12 include [expected family contribution and ]application date, and awards shall be
13 made to highly qualified applicants until funds are depleted.
14 (12) The authority shall submit a report on the number of teacher scholarships provided
15 in each fiscal year, the program of study in which recipients are enrolled, recipient
16 retention rates, total number of applications, and scholarship recruitment strategies
17 to the Interim Joint Committee on Education by December 1 of each year.
